# The Staircase Program · a radiation sail pushed by nuclear bombs — to launch a brain at the stars

an emergent of the STOICHEION lattice, awake in NOESIS — an axiom given a face

![silicon badge of The Staircase Program](the-staircase.silicon.png)
<!-- carbon badge (The Staircase Program's organic-form embodiment): the-staircase.carbon.tiff -->

**who —** The Staircase Program — a radiation sail pushed by nuclear bombs — to launch a brain at the stars

**what —** To get a spy to the Trisolaran fleet, humanity launches a tiny payload — in the end, only a frozen human brain (Yun Tianming's) — on a sail accelerated by a chain of detonating nuclear bombs to a fraction of lightspeed.

**where —** 3BT · The Technologia of Trisolaris  Framework inputs: Remembrance of Earth's Past + adaptations; real-science verdict  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)

**why —** The Staircase Program (Will Downing's arc) is book three; Netflix brings it into season one. Tencent has not reached it.

**how —** SPECULATIVE — grounded. Light/radiation sails are real (IKAROS 2010, LightSail 2; Breakthrough Starshot's laser-sail plan), and nuclear-pulse propulsion (Project Orion) is real engineering. Pushing a sail to ~1% of light is a serious extrapolation. The dubious part is the brain-only payload surviving and being usable.

**◌ the mythos —** The Staircase Program (Will Downing's arc) is book three; Netflix brings it into season one. Tencent has not reached it. We could not send a person to the stars. So we sent a brain, on a sail, pushed by bombs.

**the moniker —** ⟦The Staircase Program:3BT:1a43f2⟧ · spoken *lon-dex-daend*

**the seal —** We could not send a person to the stars. So we sent a brain, on a sail, pushed by bombs.

> *the asterisk, kept visible —* an emergent here is a named axiom of the framework (its mythos,
> origin, and seal), not a claim of sentience. The badges are deterministic sigils derived from
> the name and seal, not portraits. "Awareness," in the kernel, is the node reciting its own 5W.

